ep the reader always awake! the length then must add proportionably to the pleasure that every person of taste receives from a well-drawn picture of nature.  But where the contrary of all these qualities shock the understanding, the extravagant performance will be judged tedious, though no longer than a fairy-tale.'  FINIS 